main event: Two airline pilots observed an unidentified flying object near Great Mills, Maryland on October 19, 1959.
interesting points: The object was red, reddish-white and appeared 5-6 times larger than a star,Green wings were protruding from the object,The sighting lasted approximately 25 minutes,The airlines pilots were not available for interrogation according to the report,No follow-up was attempted due to insufficient data.
sighted object: one unidentified flying object with green wings
witness description: airline pilots from National Airlines Flight 118 and Eastern Airlines Flight 642
